title: I only upload photos with my Pixel 2's unlimited original quality backup but photos has 1.38GB used?
content:
I've gone through almost all of my photos in my Google Photos, and can't seem to find any indication as to which files are taking up space. I checked on Google Drive and Google Photos for a storage breakdown, and Google Photos is taking up 1.38GB even though I should have unlimited original quality backup. What is taking up space and how do I find the stuff that's taking up space? 

I do not have any unsupported video formats or image formats.
